{[#]} 25... b5 $1 {The most precise continuation. Black immediately challenges
White's space advantage.} 26. e4 ({A possible alternative is} 26. cxb5 axb5 {
when Black wants to proceed with ... d6-d5 followed by ...b5-b4. Therefore,
White should play} 27. e4 {Nevertheless, after} Rd7 28. Kh1 Ra8 29. R1d2 d5 30.
exd5 exd5 31. Qd3 b4 $132 {Black has sufficient counterplay.}) 26... e5 27. Rd5
bxc4 28. bxc4 Qa4 29. Rc1 Rc6 {Black managed to obtain a comfortable play. The
weaknesses on d6 and c4 balance each other.} *

