{This position is taken from the game Harutyunian - Gharibyan, 2019.} 22. g4 $1
{This is the best practical chance. As we know, in this endgame, White's main
strategy is to gain space on the kingside.} h6 23. h4 b5 $2 {This is already a
serious mistake.} ({Black should have played} 23... Nfd7 {when after} 24. Nxd7
Rxd7 25. Rxd7 Nxd7 26. Ne4 b5 27. cxb5 axb5 28. h5 $14 {/= White has only a
very tiny advantage. With a precise play, Black should be able to make an easy
draw.}) 24. b4 $1 ({In the game, White played} 24. g5 $6 hxg5 25. hxg5 {
At this point, instead of 25...Nh5, Black should have played} Nfd7 $11 {
with equality.}) 24... Ncd7 25. c5 $18 {White is strategically winning.} *

