1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. Nf3 cxd4 4. Nxd4 b6 5. Nc3 Bb7 6. f3 e6 7. e4 d6 8. Be2
a6 9. Be3 Nbd7 10. O-O Be7 11. Qd2 O-O 12. Rfd1 Rc8 13. Rac1 Qc7 14. Bf1 Rfe8
15. Kh1 Qb8 16. Qf2 Bd8 17. Nb3 Bc7 {This maneuvre bolsters the defence of the
weak pawn on b6 and adds more strenght to a potential d6-d5 break, as now the
e8-rook is uncovered and another piece is directed against White's king.} 18.
Qg1 Kh8 $1 {After White has defended against the d6-d5 break, Black switches
to the Fischer plan.} 19. Rc2 Rg8 20. Rcd2 g5 21. Bd4 Rg6 22. Nc1 (22. g4 h5
$13) 22... Rcg8 23. Nd3 Qf8 24. Re1 g4 25. fxg4 e5 26. Be3 Nxg4 27. Nd5 Bd8 28.
Nf2 Bh4 29. Ree2 Nxe3 30. Nxe3 Bxf2 31. Qxf2 Bxe4 32. Nf5 Nc5 33. Ng3 Ba8 34.
Rd1 Ne6 35. Qxb6 Nf4 36. Rf2 Qh6 37. Kg1 Qh4 38. Qb3 Rh6 39. Rxf4 exf4 40. Qc3+
f6 41. Nf5 Rxg2+ 42. Bxg2 Qxh2+ 0-1

