{A model game in the Andersson system by the world champion.} 1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4
c5 3. Nc3 e6 4. g3 b6 5. Bg2 Bb7 6. O-O Be7 7. d4 cxd4 8. Qxd4 d6 9. Bg5 a6 ({
The natural} 9... Nbd7 $2 {loses a pawn after} 10. Nb5 $1) 10. Bxf6 Bxf6 11.
Qf4 O-O (11... Bxc3 $2 12. bxc3 Qc7 13. Rfd1 Nc6 (13... e5 14. Qd2 $18) 14.
Rxd6 $16) 12. Rfd1 Be7 13. Ne4 Bxe4 14. Qxe4 Ra7 15. Nd4 Rc7 16. Rd2 Rc5 (16...
Rxc4 $2 17. Nxe6) 17. Rad1 Qc7 18. b3 Kh8 19. Qb1 Nd7 20. e3 Qc8 21. Rc2 Rc7
22. a4 Rd8 23. Qa2 $1 {Now White stands ready for b3-b4-b5.} Ne5 (23... h6 24.
b4 ({Or} 24. a5 $16) 24... Nf6 (24... Bf6 25. a5 $16) 25. b5 axb5 26. axb5 Bf8
27. Nc6 $18) 24. h3 {Preparing f2-f4.} Bf6 25. Rcd2 {After Black has taken
protection from d6, White changes plans and starts targeting that pawn again:}
Rc5 26. f4 Ng6 27. Rd3 h6 28. Qd2 e5 {An interesting attempt to create
counterplay. White now steers the game into an ending that requires exact
defence by Black.} 29. Nc2 b5 30. axb5 axb5 31. Na3 bxc4 32. Nxc4 d5 33. Bxd5
Qxh3 34. Qg2 Qxg2+ 35. Kxg2 exf4 36. exf4 Rc7 37. Ne3 $14 Rcd7 38. Ng4 Bb2 39.
Nf2 f6 40. Be4 Nf8 41. b4 Rxd3 42. Nxd3 Bc3 43. Rc1 Bd4 44. Nc5 Be3 45. Rc3
Rd2+ 46. Kf3 Bd4 47. Rc4 g6 48. Nd3 Bg1 49. Rc8 Kg7 50. Rc7+ Kg8 51. f5 g5 52.
g4 Bh2 53. Rb7 Rc2 54. Nc5 Rc3+ 55. Ke2 h5 56. gxh5 g4 57. Ne6 Rc8 58. b5 Rb8
59. Rxb8 Bxb8 60. Bd5 Ba7 61. Kf1 Be3 62. Kg2 Kf7 63. Nxf8+ Kxf8 64. Kg3 Ke7
65. Kxg4 Kd6 66. Kf3 Bd2 67. b6 1-0

