{Here Beliavsky played a model game in the Hedgehog mainline with 7...Ne4.
Despite an exchange of all four knights, he could prevent all of Black's
counterplay and slowly increase the pressure up to the breaking point.} 1. Nf3
Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 c5 4. g3 b6 5. Bg2 Bb7 6. O-O Be7 7. Re1 Ne4 8. Nxe4 Bxe4
9. d3 Bb7 10. e4 Nc6 11. d4 cxd4 12. Nxd4 Nxd4 13. Qxd4 O-O 14. Rd1 d6 $6 ({
Better is} 14... Bc6 $1 {keeping the d-pawn more solid.}) 15. a4 $1 Qc7 16. Ra2
$3 {Preparing b2-b3 and Bb2.} ({Of course not} 16. b3 $4 Bf6) 16... Bc6 17. b3
Rfd8 18. Ba3 Rd7 19. Rad2 Rad8 20. Qe3 $16 Qb7 21. f4 h6 22. h4 a6 23. Bb4 $1 {
Discouraging any b6-b5 ideas.} (23. Kh2 $2 b5 $1 24. cxb5 axb5 25. a5 b4 $132)
23... Bf8 (23... b5 24. cxb5 $1 axb5 25. a5 $16) 24. Kh2 Be7 25. Qe2 Bf8 26.
Rd3 Qa8 27. R1d2 Qb7 28. Qe1 Qa8 29. Qh1 Qc8 30. f5 Re8 31. e5 Bxg2 32. Qxg2
exf5 33. exd6 Re4 34. Qf2 b5 35. Qxf5 Qb7 36. axb5 axb5 37. Rd5 Re1 38. c5 Qa7
39. Re5 g6 40. Qxd7 1-0

