{White should remember the following move order and how to exploit it.} 1. Nf3
Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. g3 b6 4. Bg2 Bb7 5. O-O e6 6. Nc3 a6 7. Re1 d6 8. e4 Nbd7 ({
The attempt to close the position with} 8... e5 {can be answered with} 9. b4 {
, and} cxb4 10. Nd5 {, followed by a quick d2-d4, gives White more than enough
compensation for the pawn.}) 9. d4 cxd4 10. Nxd4 Qc7 {The only natural move to
protect the b7-bishop.} (10... Be7 11. e5 dxe5 (11... Bxg2 12. exf6 $18) 12.
Nxe6 fxe6 13. Bxb7 $18) 11. Nd5 $3 $16 exd5 12. exd5+ Kd8 (12... Be7 13. Nf5
Ne5 14. Nxg7+ Kf8 15. Bh6 $18) 13. Nc6+ Bxc6 14. dxc6 Nc5 (14... Nb8 15. Qf3
Be7 16. Bf4 Ra7 17. Rad1 Ne8 18. b4 $18) 15. b4 $16 Ne6 16. c5 bxc5 17. bxc5
Kc8 18. Rb1 Rb8 19. Rb7 Rxb7 20. cxb7+ Kb8 21. Qa4 Qxc5 22. Qxa6 Qa7 23. Qc6
Qc5 24. Qa4 Qa7 25. Qc4 Qc5 26. Qd3 Qd4 27. Qxd4 Nxd4 28. Be3 Ne6 29. Rb1 Be7
30. Bc6 d5 31. Rb5 Kc7 32. Ba7 Kxc6 33. b8=Q Rxb8 34. Rxb8 d4 35. a4 Nd7 36.
Rb1 Bd8 37. Kf1 d3 38. Be3 Ba5 39. Rb5 Bc3 40. Rb3 Ba5 41. Rxd3 Ndc5 42. Bxc5
Nxc5 43. Rf3 Nxa4 44. Rxf7 Bc3 1/2-1/2

