{The last typical idea which I would like to show you is b7-b5 break combined
with d5. Black sacrifices a pawn on the queen side for activity.} 21... b5 $1
22. cxb5 d5 $1 {Black sacrificing a pawn to open the position.} 23. e5 ({
More reasonable looks} 23. exd5 Nxd5 24. Nxd5 Rxd5 25. Rxc8+ Qxc8 26. Qe2 Rxd1+
27. Qxd1 axb5 28. a4 bxa4 29. bxa4 Qc3 $11 {With drawish endgame, but Victor
the Great always tries to win the game.}) 23... Nd7 24. Qe2 (24. bxa6 Nxe5 25.
Qe2 Qa7+ 26. Kg2 Nc6 $11 {[%cal Gc6b4,Gc6b8] With an interesting endgame with
mutual chances.}) (24. f4 Qa7+ 25. Kg2 axb5 26. Qxb5 Nc5 {[%cal Gd5d4] with
sufficient compensation for the pawn, for example:} 27. b4 Ne4 28. Nxe4 Rxc1
29. Rxc1 Qe3 $1 30. Qc5 Qxe4+) 24... Rc5 $1 {[%cal Gd8c8]} 25. a4 (25. bxa6
Rdc8 26. Qe3 Qxa6 27. f4 Qb6 {[%cal Gc5c3]} 28. Kg2 Qa5 29. Na4 Rc2+ 30. Kh3
R8c7 $132 {[%cal Gd5d4,Gc2a2] Activity of Black's pieces, unsecured position
of White's king and the protected passed d-pawn give Black more than enough
compensation for the pawn.}) 25... Rdc8 26. Qe3 Qb8 $1 {The beginning of
manoeuvre which allows Black to win back the pawn.} 27. f4 Qb6 $1 {[%cal Gc5c3]
} 28. Kg2 axb5 ({Of course bad is} 28... Rxb5 $2 29. Nxd5 $1 $18) 29. Kh3 $6 {
Missing Black`s reply.} (29. axb5 Qa5 30. Ne2 {was sufficient for maintain the
balance.}) 29... R5c6 $1 30. Qxb6 (30. Qf3 bxa4 31. Nxa4 Qb4 32. Rxc6 Rxc6 $15)
30... Nxb6 31. a5 Rxc3 32. axb6 $6 ({Stronger was} 32. Rxc3 $1 Rxc3 33. axb6
Rc6 34. Rc1 Rxb6 35. Kg4 {[%cal Gh2h4] with very good chances for a draw.})
32... b4 $1 33. Kg4 (33. Rxc3 $143 bxc3 34. b7 Rb8 35. Rd3 c2 36. Rc3 Rxb7 37.
Rxc2 Rxb3 {With good chances for Black to convert this endgame.}) 33... Kh7 $1
34. Rxc3 bxc3 35. Rc1 $2 {This losses.} ({Was correct} 35. Kf3 c2 36. Rc1 Rc3+
37. Kg4 Rxb3 38. Rxc2 Rxb6 39. h4 {[%cal Gh4h5] and it seems that Black hardly
can make any progress.}) 35... d4 36. Kf3 d3 37. b7 d2 $1 38. bxc8=Q dxc1=Q 39.
Qc4 Qd1+ {English Hedgehog is a very complex opening. If you learn it and
understand the main ideas and nuances you can use for many years. I hope that
you enjoy the article and learn a lot about this pawn structure. I wish you a
lot of wins with English Hedgehog. Good Luck!} 0-1

